author: Inside Edition
description: Actress Lily James, best known for playing Cinderella and Pam Anderson, is playing tech executive Whitney Wolfe, a key figure behind the success of Tinder and the founder of Bumble, in the hot new movie "Swiped." But the real Whitney Wolfe says she is flattered by James being cast to play her, but she wanted the movie shut down. Currently, Tinder has 75 million active users. Bumble has 50 million. So, will the real Wolfe watch the movie?
title: Tinder, Bumble Exec Whitney Wolfe Wanted 'Swiped' Movie Shut Down

author: Inside Edition
description: Parents say painful blisters on their teens’ hands came after their coach ordered them to do bear crawls along a hot track as punishment during majorette practice. Inside Edition spoke with 14-year-old Mar'Kayla Banks and her mother, Ronnisha. Trinity Peagler, 14, is in the hospital with second degree burns on her hands. Inside Edition showed a photo of the blisters to dermatologist Dr. Doris Day. The school says they are investigating the incident.
title: Teens Get Painful Blisters After Punishment By Dance Coach: Parents

author: Inside Edition
description: Concern is mounting over the growing use of building rooftops by snipers. On Wednesday, a gunman perched on the roof in Dallas opened fire on an ICE van and killed a detainee, then himself. Two weeks ago, Charlie Kirk was slain by an assassin authorities say was positioned on a roof at a university in Utah. The sniper who targeted President Donald Trump at a rally in Pennsylvania last year was also on a roof. Inside Edition spoke with a security expert.
title: Growing Concern Over Use Of Building Rooftops By Snipers

author: Inside Edition
description: Jimmy Kimmel was back at it Thursday night ripping into President Donald Trump for blasting his comeback. The ratings are in for Kimmel's first show back after his suspension: 6.3 million viewers, with 26 million people watching on social media. Kimmel made it clear that he was going to be as edgy as ever. Meanwhile, the president is going ballistic over the incident at the United Nations when the escalator came to a sudden stop.
title: Views For Jimmy Kimmel's 1st Show After Suspension Highest In 10 Years

author: Inside Edition
description: According to the New York Post, Kate Gosselin is now living with her former bodyguard, Steve Neild. In 2009, after starring on their hit reality tv show documenting raising eight children, Kate and her then husband Jon Gosselin split in a contentious divorce. At the time, Kate denied rumors that she was having an affair with the bodyguard. A year later, Neild was still a presence at Kate's side. John blasted his ex-wife Thursday.
title: Reality Star Kate Gosselin Reveals Relationship With Bodyguard: Report

author: Inside Edition
description: Those involved in the illegal wildlife trade aren't just trying to move creatures like big cats and rare reptiles. This coral from Indonesia is a victim too. While the smugglers may have made it on the plane and across the world with the coral, they were caught at customs. The coral was confiscated at JFK airport and sent to the NY Aquarium in Brooklyn to be cared for. Inside Edition Digital’s Mara Montalbano has more.
title: Coral Smuggled From Indonesia Now Lives At New York Aquarium

title: Dating Advice For Real-Life Golden Bachelorettes #shorts

title: Teen Influencer Zuza Beine Dies After Long Struggle With Leukemia #shorts

description: A group of divers in the Las Vegas area saw a plea from a couple on Facebook asking for help after one of them lost a wedding ring during a day on the Colorado River. One of those divers was Beate Fischer. After retracing the couple's path she found it on her first dip under the water. Inside Edition Digital’s Mara Montalbano has more.
title: Scuba Diver Returns Lost Wedding Ring Found in Colorado River
